      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Bruges City Hall"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After an enjoyable time spent at the Friet Museum, we headed over to Bruges City Hall. Admission to the City Hall is included with the Bruges City Card (see "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/2016/06/travel-with-me-bruges-in-three-days-part-1-of-1/",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "part 1"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to read about the card)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/2016-01-30-11.35.08-1024x768.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-01-30 11.35.08",
              "title": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Bruges City Hall sits in Burg Square, one of the more popular squares in the city. Part of the building that stands today was built in 1421 during a time when Bruges was very powerful both economically and politically. The building's interior was restored in the early 20th century, and it is stunning!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/20160130_114803-1024x576.jpg",
              "alt": "20160130_114803",
              "title": null
            },
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/20160130_114803.jpg",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " "
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/2016-01-30-11.41.58-1024x768.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-01-30 11.41.58",
              "title": null
            },
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/2016-01-30-11.41.58.jpg",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After admiring the gorgeous architecture and decor of city hall, we walked through the city museum housed in a room just off of the main room."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Next door to city hall sits an old mansion that now houses the city archives and a courtroom. Called Brugse Vrije (Liberty of Bruges), it is worth the short stop to see the stunning carvings and fireplace in the old courtroom. This is also included with the Bruges City Card (and also included if you pay for a City Hall ticket) which makes the short stop seem more worth it."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/20160130_120803-1024x576.jpg",
              "alt": "20160130_120803",
              "title": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Belgian Waffles"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "I did some research on the place to get the best Belgian waffles and stumbled across a cute tea room that served lunch and waffles. One fun fact we learned from a local is that locals never have Belgian waffles for a meal as they are typically an afternoon snack. We were still determined to eat some, and it worked out for us to have them as a meal, but we were definitely the only people in the restaurant having waffles for lunch. :)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/2016-01-30-12.40.28-1024x768.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-01-30 12.40.28",
              "title": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/20160130_124020-1024x576.jpg",
              "alt": "20160130_124020",
              "title": null
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Walking Around Town"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "As I've already mentioned, Bruges is best enjoyed by roaming the streets and peeking into the shops. We spent some time doing that this day, and we ran across my favorite Christmas shop, Kathe Wohlfahrt! It was closed for the season, but the window brought back memories of when we visited the flagship store in Rothenburg ob Tauber in Germany in December 2015. I still haven't written about that trip on the blog, but I plan to at some point this year!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
