          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " The beautiful arch over Blinde Ezelstraat (Blind Donkey Street)[/caption]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Yet another icon in Bruges is the beautiful handmade lace. Our guide showed us this window of one of the few remaining handmade lace shops in the city. According to her, most of the shops in Bruges these days sell lace made in China and not the handmade lace most people are looking for. There is obviously a price difference, but if you want real handmade lace, seek out the legitimate shops by asking a local or by purchasing lace from the Lace Center museum shop on Peperstraat."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
