          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". That's a shame because it was one of our favorite Airbnbs of the whole trip. With two bedrooms, it had way more space than we needed, but the location was walking distance to the main squares, the apartment was very clean and comfortable, and the hosts were very informative and kind. They have a binder full of tips and tricks for your stay, and they had a few local beers waiting for us when we arrived. Click "
